to install laravel ,you need another program called composer.
so you must install composer frist.....

$ php -r "copy('https://getcomposer.org/installer', 'composer-setup.php');"

install check: ls -al   commend

$ php -r "if (hash_file('SHA384', 'composer-setup.php') === '544e09ee996cdf60ece3804abc52599c22b1f40f4323403c44d44fdfdd586475ca9813a858088ffbc1f233e9b180f061') { echo 'Installer verified'; } else { echo 'Installer corrupt'; unlink('composer-setup.php'); } echo PHP_EOL;"

$ php composer-setup.php

install check: ls -al   commend

$ php -r "unlink('composer-setup.php');"

now, composer already installed.

check... php composer.phar 


version check::

$ php composer.phar --version

now, install laravel::::::::::::::::::::
ctrl+h hidden file show commend. home e .config file check

$ php composer.phar global require "laravel/installer"

if Installation failed, deleting ./composer.json.  ase....tahole install...now

$ sudo apt-get install   php     exm :php7.1-zip

agin commend::: $ php composer.phar global require "laravel/installer"

laravel already installed.

the next step create laravel project in /var/www/html

wops,i not install apache2 now,i will frist install apache2::: jodi var file e www file na thakle ....tahole apache2 install korte hobe
$ sudo apt-get install apache2

the next step create laravel project in /var/www/html

$ php composer.phar create-project --prefer-dist laravel/laravel blog or

$ php composer.phar create-project --prefer-dist laravel/laravel /var/www/html/blog


then in project inside mustbe server start:::serve start commend
$ php artisan serve

example:: var/www/html/blog project inside : terminal not stop ,if server on. 
























 
